The finite difference equations form a **tridiagonal system** $A\mathbf{y} = \mathbf{b}$:
\[
\begin{pmatrix}
d_1 & u_1 & 0 & \cdots & 0 \\
l_2 & d_2 & u_2 & \cdots & 0 \\
0 & l_3 & d_3 & \ddots & \vdots \\
\vdots & \ddots & \ddots & \ddots & u_{N-2} \\
0 & \cdots & 0 & l_{N-1} & d_{N-1}
\end{pmatrix}
\begin{pmatrix}
y_1 \\ y_2 \\ y_3 \\ \vdots \\ y_{N-1}
\end{pmatrix}
=
\begin{pmatrix}
b_1 \\ b_2 \\ b_3 \\ \vdots \\ b_{N-1}
\end{pmatrix}
\]
where for $i = 1, \ldots, N-1$:
$$
l_i &= 1 - \frac{hp_i}{2} \\
d_i &= -2 + h^2 q_i \\
u_i &= 1 + \frac{hp_i}{2} \\
b_i &= h^2 r_i - \delta_{i,1}l_1\alpha - \delta_{i,N-1}u_{N-1}\beta
$$
The boundary terms $\alpha$ and $\beta$ modify only $b_1$ and $b_{N-1}$.
